# HTMX Path-Params Pattern

Use the **path-params** extension to drive URL parameters from events and reload content. Do not use template literals or hardcoded values for dynamic path segments.

## Rules

- Use `{agent}` and `{version}` placeholders in `hx-get` URLs, not `agents/${agentId}/versions/${version}`.
- Fill values via `hx-vals` from the triggering event or DOM data attributes.
- Use `hx-trigger` for event-driven reloads (e.g. `agent-selected from:body`, `resource-updated from:body`).
- Ensure `hx-ext="path-params"` is set on a parent element (e.g. `body`).

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - placeholders + event-driven values
hx-get="agents/{agent}/versions/{version}/resources/pane"
hx-vals="js:{ agent: event?.detail?.agent, version: event?.detail?.version }"
hx-trigger="agent-selected from:body, resource-updated from:body"

// ✅ GOOD - placeholders + values from DOM (for click-triggered requests)
data-agent={agentId}
data-version={version}
// ... on child:
hx-vals="js:(()=>{const p=document.getElementById('resources-pane');return{agent:p?.dataset?.agent,version:p?.dataset?.version};})()"

// ❌ BAD - template literals / constants
hx-get={`agents/${agentId}/versions/${version}/resources/pane`}
```
